-grandchildren.%3Cp%3ESue%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESue%20Miller%2C%2083%2C%20raised%20children%2C%20grandchildren%2C%20and%20great-grandchildren%20mostly%20on%20her%20own.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20retirement%2C%20Miller%20returned%20to%20work%20as%20a%20part-time%20lunch%20lady%20in%20a%20local%20school%20district.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20cancer%2C%20Miller%20remains%20active%2C%20aiming%20to%20live%20until%20100%20for%20her%20grandson's%20sake.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Sue%20Miller%2C%2083%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Wisconsin.%20Miller%20raised%20three%20children%2C%20two%20grandchildren%2C%20and%20two%20great-grandchildren%2C%20much%20of%20which%20was%20on%20her%20own.%20Miller%20now%20lives%20alone%20near%20her%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcatered-my-son-every-whim-he-has-little-self-esteem-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eautistic%20son%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20works%20as%20a%20lunch%20lady.%20This%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20blessed%20because%20even%20when%20things%20were%20really%20hard%2C%20it%20always%20seemed%20like%20something%20came%20up%20to%20help%20me%20out.%20There%20was%20always%20some%20job%20for%20me.%20I've%20always%20been%20a%20survivor.%20How%20can%20I%20see%20it%20any%20differently%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20three%20kids%2C%2011%20months%20and%2015%20months%20apart.%20My%20middle%20child%2C%20David%2C%20is%20autistic.%20He%20didn't%20walk%20until%20he%20was%20three%20and%20was%20extremely%20hyperactive.%20I%20was%20lucky%20if%20we%20got%20four%20hours%20of%20sleep%20a%20night.%20He's%20smart%20and%20understands%2C%20but%20he%20was%20always%20on%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparent-raising-grandchild-work-ret