0he'd%20snuggle%20up%20next%20to%20me%20and%20squeeze%20my%20arm%20until%20he%20fell%20asleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20went%20somewhere%2C%20I%20always%20took%20the%20kids%20with%20me.%20I%20had%20car%20seats%20in%20my%20car%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7078a72-a2c5-42e1-9092-90d6250231f3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20retired%20at%2065%20after%20a%20layoff%20from%20my%20accounting%20job%20at%20a%20deli%20meat%20processing%20plant%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20work%20for%20about%20seven%20years%20until%20January%202014.%20My%20stepmother%20had%20a%20mild%20stroke%2C%20so%20I%20moved%20back%20to%20Wisconsin%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her.%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20so%20I%20was%20still%20able%20to%20help%20Christie%20live%20in%20Arizona%20until%20my%20daughter%20moved%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoving%20also%20gave%20me%20the%20chance%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20David%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20a%20group%20home.%20He's%2062%20now.%20I%20pick%20him%20up%20on%20weekends%2C%20and%20we%20go%20for%20lunch%20or%20shopping.%20Every%20caregiver%20just%20loves%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visit%20Arizona%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20moving%20back%20here%20was%20necessary.%20I%20wish%20I%20could%20be%20in%20both%20places%20at%20once.%20I%20especially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-retirement-social-security-caregiving-financial-struggles-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiss%20my%20great-grandsons%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they're%20so%20far%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2247b1e0b5-4dc8-4a7e-b07b-ffefe7ab67bc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20as%20a%20volunteer%20and%20ended%20up%20becoming%20a%20lunch%20lady%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustles-entrepreneurship-cost-to-start-small-business-capitalism-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20part-ti