22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeon%20Black%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20entrusted%20him%20with%20managing%20their%20finances%20and%20ensuring%20their%20tax%20bills%20stayed%20as%20low%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department's%20files%20show%20that%20in%20the%20years%20before%20his%202019%20arrest%20on%20sex-trafficking%20charges%20and%20jailhouse%20death%2C%20Epstein%20tried%20to%20nab%20another%20billionaire%20client%3A%20the%20real%20estate%20and%20media%20mogul%20Mortimer%20Zuckerman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman%2C%20who%20is%20now%2088%2C%20at%20one%20point%20had%20a%20higher%20public%20profile%20than%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-brad-karp-surveillance-leon-black-accuser-extortion-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlack%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20and%20chairman%20of%20Apollo%20Global%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-billionaires-named-in-the-epstein-files-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWexner%2C%20the%20onetime%20owner%20of%20Victoria's%20Secret%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20the%201980s%20and%202000s%2C%20Zuckerman%20was%20a%20frequent%20presence%20on%20cable%20news%2C%20occasionally%20floated%20himself%20as%20a%20national%20political%20candidate%2C%20and%20saw%20his%20romantic%20flings%20chronicled%20in%20tabloid%20newspapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20now%20worth%20about%20%242.7%20billion%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fprofile%2Fmortimer-zuckerman%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Forbes%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20company%20Boston%20Properties%20and%20previously%20owned%20media%20outlets%20including%20The%20Atlantic%2C%20the%20New%20York%20Daily%20News%2C%20and%20Fast%20Company.%20He%20stepped%20away%20from%20some%20of%20those%20companies%20and%20public%20life%20about%20a%20decade%20ago%20%26quot%3Bdue%20to%20issues%20with%20his%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20person%20close%20to%20Zuckerman's%20family%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20still%20owns%20US%20News%20%26amp%3B%20World%20Report%2C%20best%20known%20for%20its%20rankings%20of%20universities%20and%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20men%20in%20suits%20and%20tuxedos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab06331fb3fcb426490fce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMort%20Zuckerman%2C%20middle%2C%20in%202007%20with%20then-NYC%20Mayor%20Michael%20Bloomberg%3Cp%3EPatrick%20McMullan%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman's%20relationship%20with%20Epstein%20stretched%20back%20to%20at%20least%20the%20early%202000s.%20In%202003%2C%20they%20teamed%20up%20with%20producer%20Harvey%20Weinstein%20and%20writer%20Michael%20Wolff%20in%20a%20failed%20bid%20to%20buy%20New%20York%20magazine.%20In%202004%2C%20Zuckerman%20and%20Epstein%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2004%2F10%2F18%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fzuckerman-and-financier-to-back-pop-culture-magazine.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinanced%20the%20ill-fated%20relaunch%20of%20Radar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20celebrity%20gossip%20publication.%20The%20Epstein%20files%20show%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-birthday-book-messages-business-leaders-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerman%20contributed%20to%20Epstein's%20now-famous%2050th%20birthday%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%2C%20on%20at%20least%20one%20occasion%2C%20Epstein%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252011%2FEFTA02442959.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffered%20to%20set%20Zuckerman%20up%20with%20a%20woman%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20no%20indication%20in%20the%20files%20that%20Zuckerman%20had%20knowledge%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-victim-lawsuits-bank-of-america-bny-mellon-judge-skeptical-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein's%20sex%20trafficking%20operation%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20Epstein%20pitched%20himself%20to%20Zuckerman%20as%20a%20financial%20manager%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20deal%20was%20never%20consummated%2C%20but%20the%20files%20show%20that%20Epstein%2C%20a%20college%20dropout%2C%20held%20himself%20out%20as%20one%20of%20the%20few%20people%20qualified%20to%20help%20Zuckerman%20with%20what%20he%20said%20were%20sophisticated%20financial%20problems%20that%20required%20%26quot%3Bsurgical%26quot%3B%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20tried%20to%20convince%20Zuckerman%20to%20trust%20him%20above%20other%20people%20in%20his%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20act%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20Epstein%20obtained%20deeply%20personal%20information%20about%20the%20billionaire's%20health%2C%20finances%2C%20and%20family%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20used%20to%20try%20to%20convince%20the%20people%20around%20the%20billionaire%20to%20put%20him%20in%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20repeated%20rejections%20over%20the%20course%20of%20two%20years%2C%20Epstein%20turned%20impatient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hav%20not%20asked%20for%20the%20money%20that%20mort%20promised%20for%20getting%20my%20help%20and%20never%20following%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Zuckerman's%20nephews%2C%20who%20also%20served%20as%20his%20investment%20advisors.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20also%20appreciate%20you%20putting%20a%20brake%20on%20the%20daily%20news%20calling%20me%20a%20pedophile.%20I%20have%20been%20patient%20and%20my%20fondness%20for%20mort%20remains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.getkino.com%2Fdocuments%2FEFTA00585770.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20draft%20contract%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dated%20December%2017%2C%202013%2C%20shows%20that%20Epstein%20proposed%20Zuckerman%20retain%20Southern%20Trust%20Inc.%2C%20one%20of%20Epstein's%20companies%20in%20the%20US%20Virgin%20Islands%2C%20for%20%26quot%3Banalyzing%2C%20evaluating%2C%20planning%20and%20structuring%20large%20discrete%20issues%20relating%20to%20Mr.%20Zuckerman's%20financial%20estate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman%20would%20pay%20%2421%20million%20for%20the%20first%2010%20months%20of%20Epstein's%20services.%20Paul%20Weiss%2C%20the%20Big%20Law%20firm%20that%20had%20also%20done%20estate%20planning%20work%20for%20Black%2C%20would%20represent%20Zuckerman's%20interests%20in%20the%20deal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00377699.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20another%20document%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Terje%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen%2C%20a%20Norwegian%20diplomat%20and%20friend%20of%20Epstein's%2C%20would%20get%20%241%20million%20under%20the%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ER%C3%B8d-Larsen's%20role%20in%20the%20potential%20arrangement%20is%20unclear%20from%20the%20documents.%20John%20Christian%20Elden%2C%20an%20attorney%20for%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Zuckerman%20and%20the%20diplomat%20were%20friends%2C%20and%20that%20his%20role%20in%20Zuckerman's%20estate%20planning%20was%20Epstein's%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Zuckerman%20did%20not%20pursue%20Mr.%20Epstein's%20advice%20or%20proposals%2C%20and%20accordingly%2C%20these%20arrangements%20were%20never%20implemented%2C%26quot%3B%20Elden%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222969%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jeffrey%20epstein%20censored%20face%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8a745d3e2f1aef36a0189%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222277%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%20died%20in%20prison%20in%202019%20while%20awaiting%20trial%20on%20sex-trafficking%20charges.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Epstein%20files%20show%20that%20he%20began%20getting%20involved%20with%20Zuckerman's%20estate%20planning%20earlier%20in%202013.%20That%20April%20%E2%80%94%20following%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252010%2FEFTA01786087.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20dinner%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Zuckerman%20at%20Epstein's%20Manhattan%20mansion%20that%2C%20according%20his%20calendar%2C%20also%20featured%20Ehud%20Barak%2C%20Jes%20Staley%2C%20Woody%20Allen%2C%20and%20Tom%20Pritzker%20%E2%80%94%20Epstein%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252010%2FEFTA02035370.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Zuckerman%3C%2Fa%3E%20he'd%20review%20his%20financial%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20subsequent%20weeks%2C%20Zuckerman%20sent%20Epstein%20hundreds%20of%20pages%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.getkino.com%2Fdocuments%2FEFTA00963650.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epersonal%20financial%20information%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20detailed%20valuations%20of%20his%20assets%2C%20documentation%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-reveal-how-billionaires-spend-money-mortimer-zuckerman-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espending%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20structures%20of%20his%20trusts%2C%20his%20charitable%20contributions%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.getkino.com%2Fdocuments%2FEFTA01120720.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edetails%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20his%20separation%20agreement%20with%20his%20ex-wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman's%20finances%20were%20in%20a%20dismal%20state%2C%20Epstein%20told%20him%20in%20a%20June%202013%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trusts%20needed%20a%20%26quot%3Btotal%20re-do%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20said.%20The%20job%20required%20someone%20with%20knowledge%20of%20investing%2C%20tax%2C%20estate%20law%2C%20real%20estate%20partnerships%2C%20securities%20filings%2C%20and%20divorce%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3Bit%20is%20a%20serious%20job%20that%20requires%20surgical%20intervention%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20initially%20said%20it%20would%20take%20him%2015%20months%20to%20personally%20fix%20Zuckerman's%20finances%20and%20cost%20between%20%2430%20million%20and%20%2440%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00963042.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20email%20two%20days%20later%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Epstein%20made%20an%20emotional%20appeal%20to%20Zuckerman%20to%20listen%20to%20his%20advice%2C%20leaning%20on%20memories%20of%20their%20long%20relationship%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMort%20%2C%20I%20have%20sat%20with%20you%20in%20dunkin%20donuts%20outside%20of%20sloan%20kettering%20bad%20time%20%2C--%20sat%20next%20to%20you%20at%20harry%20evans%20when%20you%20announced%20your%20engagement%20to%20Marla%2C%20hopeful%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20month%2C%20after%20phone%20calls%20and%20meetings%2C%20Epstein%20urged%20Zuckerman%20to%20move%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20had%20everything%20%26quot%3Bready%20to%20go%26quot%3B%20as%20soon%20as%20Zuckerman%20agreed%20to%20hire%20him.%20If%20Zuckerman%20delayed%2C%20Epstein%20warned%2C%20%26quot%3Bhundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%26quot%3B%20would%20be%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverything%20virtually%20from%20top%20to%20bottom%20will%20get%20redone.%20every%20trust%20%2C%20all%20investments%20%2C%20and%20build%20a%20financial%20structure%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20said%20with%20his%20typical%20idiosyncratic%20punctuation.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20time%20required%20to%20fix%20and%20time%20getting%20shorter%20to%20fix%20it%20%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20file%20by%20the%20end%20of%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00967200.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAugust%202013%2C%20Epstein%20told%20his%20personal%20lawyer%20and%20accountant%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Zuckerman%20agreed%20to%20a%20%2430%20million%20fee%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20draft%20a%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20emails%20to%20Epstein%2C%20Zuckerman%20was%20noncommittal%2C%20and%20Epstein%20shifted%20his%20approach.%20In%20a%20September%202013%20email%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00871628.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edisparaged%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20team%20Zuckerman%20had%20surrounded%20himself%20with%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Zuckerman's%20nephews%20and%20investment%20advisors%2C%20Eric%20and%20Jamie%20Gertler.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMort%20%2C%20I%20recommend%20you%20hire%20professionals%20%2C%20not%20your%20nephews.%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252010%2FEFTA01951148.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerman%20needed%20an%20%26quot%3Barchitect%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20financial%20life%2C%20and%20that%20leaving%20his%20nephews%20in%20charge%20would%20cause%20family%20strife.%20In%20Epstein's%20view%2C%20putting%20Zuckerman's%20nephew%20in%20charge%20of%20his%20daughter's%20upbringing%20would%20%26quot%3Bwreak%20havoc%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Zuckerman%20failed%20to%20sign%20the%20%2421%20million%20contract%20by%20the%20end%20of%202013%20despite%20Esptein's%20warnings%20of%20dire%20tax%20consequences%2C%20the%20convicted%20sex%20offender%20tried%20to%20salvage%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mort%20Zuckerman%2C%20left%2C%20at%20a%20gala%20in%20in%20NYC%20in%202016%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab06c21fb3fcb426490fe0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMort%20Zuckerman%2C%20left%2C%20at%20a%20gala%20in%20NYC%20in%202016.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20January%202014%20email%2C%20Epstein%20told%20Zuckerman%20that%20he%20had%20already%20sunk%20resources%20into%20the%20project%2C%20stressed%20the%20supposedly%20dire%20straits%20of%20Zuckerman's%20finances%2C%20and%20told%20Zuckerman%20he%20would%20be%20getting%20Epstein%20at%20a%20bargain%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20only%20have%20good%20feelings%20towards%20you%2C%20and%20am%20torn%20watching%20you%20do%20yourself%20financial%20harm%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00684769.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252011%2FEFTA02336511.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerman%20told%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20financial%20structure%20he%20suggested%20just%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20fit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJeffrey.%20I%20have%20now%20consulted%20with%20three%20tax%20specialists%20and%20they%20do%20not%20see%20the%20issues%20as%20you%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerman%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20didn't%20give%20up.%20Following%20a%20June%202014%20breakfast%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%252010%2FEFTA01912143.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20wrote%20Zuckerman%20a%20long%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bin%20order%20to%20memorialize%20our%20conversation.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20Zuckerman%20had%20told%20him%20he%20believed%20his%20estate-planning%20capability%20%26quot%3Bwas%20only%20decreasing%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20delegate%20responsibility%20to%20a%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20agree%20that%20a%20committee%20should%20be%20set%20up%20to%20manage%20your%20financial.%20affairs%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote.%20%26quot%3Byour%20statement%20that%20you%20realize%20you%20are%20no%20longer%20capable%20of%20doing%20so%20.%20You%20suggested%20that%20Terje%20larson%20be%20in%20charge%20as%20you%20fully%20trust%20his%20judgement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20email%2C%20Epstein%20yet%20again%20pitched%20that%20he%20be%20put%20in%20charge%2C%20and%20suggested%20he%20could%20be%20paid%20with%20Boston%20Properties%20stock%20or%20part%20of%20Zuckerman's%20investment%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerman%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bdefinitely%20going%20to%20proceed%26quot%3B%20with%20putting%20together%20a%20committee%2C%20led%20by%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen%2C%20to%20run%20his%20financial%20affairs.%20There's%20no%20indication%20he%20ever%20did.%20When%20Epstein%20followed%20up%20the%20next%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00994571.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZuckerman%20told%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bi%20have%20my%20own%20pace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Terje%20Roed%20Rod%20Larsen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a8a69f1fb3fcb42648ef71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221994%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETerje%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen.%3Cp%3ETheo%20Wargo%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Global%20Citizen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20this%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00702922.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20started%20emailing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20people%20close%20to%20Zuckerman%20to%20convince%20them%20that%20he%20should%20be%20hired.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00702922.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Gertlers%2C%20he%20suggested%20Zuckerman%20only%20backed%20out%20of%20an%20agreement%20for%20Epstein%20to%20be%20his%20financial%20manager%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Bhis%20illness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20awkward%20having%20to%20remind%20you%20of%20the%20role%20I%20played%2C%20expenses%20I%20incurred%2C%20agreements%20that%20were%20reached%20(%20ask%20Terje%20larsen)%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20the%20one%20that%20uncovered%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20in%20errors%20in%20his%20financial%20reporting.%20work%20done%20at%20his%20request.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Gertler%20kept%20a%20firm%20but%20polite%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20aware%20of%20the%20uncovering%20of%20the%20financial%20errors%20but%20do%20know%20that%20any%20of%20the%20suggestions%20of%20your%20advisors%20had%20been%20previously%20considered%20or%20previously%20implemented%20by%20Mort's%20lawyers%20and%20financial%20advisors%2C%26quot%3B%20Gertler%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BRegardless%2C%20I%20am%20not%20interested%20in%20nor%20is%20it%20appropriate%20to%20go%20back%20and%20forth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202015%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00714425.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20emailed%20Eric%20Gertler%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20suggest%20that%20he%20and%20Jamie%20Gertler%20take%20over%20Zuckerman's%20financial%20life%20entirely%2C%20citing%20the%20billionaire's%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00844232.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20emailed%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20different%20plan%20to%20help%20run%20Zuckerman's%20finances%20with%20the%20help%20of%20the%20nephews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suggested%20setting%20up%20%26quot%3BMort%26quot%3B%20like%20a%20company.%20R%C3%B8d-Larsen%20and%20%26quot%3BHarry%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20possible%20reference%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-accountant-harry-beller-cash-withdrawals-jpmorgan-congress-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarry%20Beller%2C%20one%20of%20Epstein's%20in-house%20accountants%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20co-chairmen.%20Epstein%20would%20handle%20finances.%20Eric%20Gertler%20would%20run%20the%20day-to-day%20and%20health%20issues.%20And%20Jamie%20Gertler%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F02%2F14%2Fus%2Fhow-former-nyc-schools-chief-joel-klein-became-friendly-with-epstein.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoel%20Klein%2C%20another%20friend%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20oversee%20issues%20related%20to%20his%20children.%20Neither%20Beller%20nor%20Klein%20responded%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00843756.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereached%20out%20directly%20to%20Zuckerman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recommending%20that%20a%20team%20of%20people%20take%20over%2C%20but%20Zuckerman%20continued%20to%20decline%20his%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAm%20well%20on%20the%20way%20to%20completing%20the%20planning%20I%20need%20including%20the%20designation%20of%20appropriate%20representatives%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerman%20told%20him.%20%26quot%3BHave%20discussed%20it%20with%20various%20friends%20And.%20Lawyers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20Epstein's%20tone%20turned%20harsh.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00639339.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20email%20to%20the%20nephews%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20weeks%20after%20Zuckerman's%20rejection%2C%20Epstein%20suggested%20Zuckerman%20was%20taking%20drugs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3Bi%20assume%20you%20are%20aware%20that%20hes%20now%20wacko%20on%20somethings%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20late%202016%2C%20their%20relationship%20seemed%20to%20have%20deteriorated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fepstein%2Ffiles%2FDataSet%25209%2FEFTA00816149.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEpstein%20told%20Zuckerman%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3Bhow%20you%20could%20let%20your%20paper%20call%20me%20a%20pedophile.%3F%3F%3F!!!I%20expect%20a%20public%20apology%20and%20a%20full%20retraction.%20.%20I%20have%20been%20a%20close%20friend%20of%20yours%20for%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20files%20don't%20include%20a%20response%20from%20Zuckerman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-files-playbook-landing-billionaire-clients-mort-zuckerman-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772960401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab1ee7d3e2f1aef36a2548%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-files-playbook-landing-billionaire-clients-mort-zuckerman-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20his%20billionaire%20friend%20Mort%20Zuckerman's%20health%20declined%2C%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20proposed%20taking%20over%20his%20finances.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40businessinsider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-files-playbook-landing-billionaire-clients-mort-zuckerman-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20price%20hikes%20to%20working%20with%20chip%20brokers%2C%20Framework's%20CEO%20tells%20us%20how%20he's%20navigating%20the%20memory%20shortage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Framework%20CEO%20Nirav%20Patel%20is%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a9fef5fd4fbd083f299f2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20look%20at%20capitalism%20as%20a%20machine%20and%20accept%20it%20for%20what%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Framework%20CEO%20Nirav%20Patel%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3Cp%3EFramework%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPC%20maker%20Framework%20has%20raised%20prices%20multiple%20times%20as%20the%20memory%20shortage%20drags%20on.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECEO%20Nirav%20Patel%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20his%20strategy%20as%20he%20navigates%20rising%20chip%20costs%20and%20supply%20crunches.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20price%20is%20what%20it%20is%2C%20unfortunately%2C%26quot%3B%20Patel%20said.%20He%20said%20his%20goal%20was%20to%20stay%20in%20production.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-shortage-chips-cost-laptop-pc-prices-increase-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ememory%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20making%20it%20more%20expensive%20to%20build%20consumer%20electronics.%20So%2C%20without%20the%20supply-chain%20leverage%20of%20a%20tech%20giant%2C%20how%20does%20a%20startup%20making%20computers%20survive%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20put%20the%20question%20to%20Nirav%20Patel%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Framework%2C%20a%20small%20PC%20company%20with%20a%20cult%20following%20that%20sells%20modular%20computers.%20Its%20business%20also%20relies%20on%20memory%20chips%2C%20which%20are%20facing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-demis-hassabis-memory-shortage-ai-supply-chain-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eglobal%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20companies%20grow%20their%20compute%20needs%2C%20hyperscalers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-chip-shortage-bad-news-smartphone-pc-industry-ai-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edemanding%20more%20memory%20chips%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20three%20primary%20producers%3A%20Samsung%2C%20Micron%2C%20and%20SK%20Hynix.%20That's%20caused%20prices%20to%20increase%20and%20supply%20to%20be%20tied%20up%20in%20long-term%20contracts%20that%20can%20put%20smaller%20electronics%20companies%20at%20the%20back%20of%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Q%26amp%3BA%2C%20Framework's%20CEO%20walked%20Business%20Insider%20through%20how%20the%20company%20is%20navigating%20the%20challenge%2C%20from%20raising%20prices%20to%20trying%20to%20be%20as%20transparent%20as%20possible%20around%20the%20issue%20while%20maintaining%20a%20sense%20of%20scrappiness.%20This%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow'd%20you%20get%20to%20Framework%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20started%20out%20as%20part%20of%20the%20founding%20team%20at%20Oculus.%20We%20were%20standing%20up%20and%20defining%20an%20entirely%20new%20product%20category.%20Consumer%20VR%20had%20at%20that%20point%20never%20really%20been%20a%20thing%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20behind%20Framework%20was%20jumping%20to%20the%20absolute%20opposite%20end%20of%20consumer%20electronics%2C%20going%20to%20the%20most%20mature%20product%20categories.%20It%20was%20so%20mature%20that%20the%20innovation%20has%20been%20squeezed%20out%20of%20it%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20got%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-to-buy-oculus-rift-for-2-billion-2014-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20by%20Facebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20into%20Oculus%2C%20we%20all%20had%20five-year%20handcuffs.%20It%20was%20clear%20that%20staying%20at%20Facebook%20was%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20right%20move.%20It%20was%20a%20massive%20swing%20from%20being%20able%20to%20iterate%20really%20rapidly%20to%20being%20part%20of%20a%20giant%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20big%20is%20the%20company%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20We're%20a%2075-person%20company%20now%20across%20the%20US%20and%20Taiwan.%20We've%20raised%20three%20rounds%20of%20funding%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20last%20six%20years.%20The%20last%20round%20was%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20over%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20we've%20been%20operating%20in%20a%20financially%20self-sufficient%20mode%20since%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet's%20dig%20into%20memory.%20When%20did%20you%20start%20noticing%20the%20shortage%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20We%20started%20getting%20early%20indications%20of%20this%20pretty%20early%20last%20year.%20Our%20suppliers%20were%20flagging%20to%20us%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20there's%20something%20coming%20on%20the%20horizon%20in%20terms%20of%20supply-demand%20mismatch.%26quot%3B%20The%20speed%20and%20slope%20of%20that%20ascent%20were%20pretty%20unexpected%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20we%20started%20to%20get%20much%20clearer%20indications%20from%20our%20suppliers%3A%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20supply%20is%20going%20to%20be%20a%20problem.%20Get%20your%20orders%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20startup%2C%20so%20we%20can't%20do%20things%20like%20stockpile%20memory%20and%20storage.%20We're%20not%20at%20a%20scale%20where%20that%20makes%20sense.%20We%20obviously%20made%20sure%20to%20stay%20in%20very%20close%20contact%20with%20our%20suppliers%2C%20and%20to%20do%20things%20like%20test%20that%20we%20can%20get%20compatibility%20with%20as%20many%20different%20memory%20storage%20options%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221890%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20RAM%20sticks%20used%20in%20Framework's%20PCs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab43e4d3e2f1aef36a2b9e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFramework%20relies%20on%20RAM%2C%20sticks%20of%20memory%2C%20for%20its%20PCs.%3Cp%3EFramework%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20there%20any%20way%20to%20avoid%20high%20prices%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20price%20is%20what%20it%20is%2C%20unfortunately.%20It's%20no%20longer%20about%20maintaining%20the%20pricing%20you%20want.%20It's%20about%3A%20Can%20I%20get%20access%20to%20the%20supply%20to%20be%20able%20to%20continue%20to%20manufacture%20products%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20been%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20production%20on%20all%20of%20our%20products.%20A%20big%20part%20of%20that%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20scale%20that%20we're%20operating%20at.%20We%20are%20big%20enough%20to%20have%20direct%20contact%20and%20direct%20relationships%20with%20memory%20suppliers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-memory-shortage-supercuycle-stocks-to-watch-chip-semiconductor-demand-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elike%20Micron%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20we're%20small%20enough%20that%20we%20get%20to%20be%20a%20bit%20more%20flexible%20and%20creative%20than%20some%20of%20the%20bigger%20companies.%20If%20a%20broker%20comes%20to%20us%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20found%205%2C000%20memory%20modules%20in%20a%20warehouse%2C%20do%20you%20want%20them%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20we%20can%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BYeah.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20bigger%20consumer%20electronics%20companies%20have%20it%20easier%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20They%20do.%20If%20you're%20a%20Dell%2C%20HP%2C%20Lenovo%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmemory-chip-shortage-apple-earnings-first-quarter-tim-cook-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eor%20Apple%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you've%20got%20these%20very%20substantial%20long-term%20relationships%20already%20in%20place.%20You%20are%20going%20to%20be%20near%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20getting%20access%20to%20any%20allocation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETell%20me%20about%20leadership.%20How%20do%20you%20lead%20a%20team%20while%20this%20is%20happening%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20A%20big%20part%20of%20this%20for%20us%20is%20transparency%2C%20both%20internally%20and%20externally.%20Within%20company%20town%20halls%2C%20we%20maintain%20complete%20transparency%20around%20what%20our%20financial%20situation%20is%20and%20what%20our%20supply%20position%20is.%20We%20give%20people%20the%20confidence%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20aware%20if%20anything%20is%20going%20to%20become%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20think%20employees%20are%20feeling%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20There's%20a%20mentality%20of%3A%20We%20have%20an%20aligned%20mission%20and%20we%20have%20the%20right%20people%20to%20attack%20it%20together.%20It%20is%20motivating%20to%20see%20people%20come%20together%20as%20a%20team%20and%20address%20big%20problems.%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20creative%20problem-solving%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20that%20teamwork%2C%20camaraderie%2C%20and%20collaboration%20mean%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20startup%2C%20that%20you%20can%20navigate%20challenging%20situations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221884%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Framework%20PC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69ab4269d3e2f1aef36a2b66%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221376%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFramework's%20desktop%20PC.%20The%20PC%20maker%20raised%20desktop%20prices%2C%20citing%20the%20memory%20shortage%3Cp%3EFramework%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet's%20talk%20about%20price%20increases%20for%20your%20products.%20Take%20me%20behind%20the%20first%20one%3B%20how%20do%20you%20make%20the%20initial%20choice%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20big%20thing%20for%20us%20was%20looking%20at%20the%20speed%20of%20the%20increase%20in%20pricing%20from%20our%20suppliers%2C%20and%20knowing%20we've%20reached%20a%20threshold%20we%20can't%20absorb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20selling%20memory%20directly%20as%20modules%20in%20the%20Framework%20marketplace%2C%20we%20were%20the%20cheapest%20source%20of%20memory%20anywhere%20on%20the%20market.%20People%20were%20coming%20in%20and%20just%20buying%20memory%20from%20us%2C%20and%20not%20buying%20our%20computers.%20One%20very%20early%20move%20we%20made%20was%20pulling%20the%20standalone%20memory%20off%20our%20marketplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20also%20reselling%20memory%20at%20the%20price%20we're%20purchasing%20it%20at.%20We%20don't%20want%20to%20make%20money%20on%20memory%20in%20this%20environment.%20What%20we%20want%20to%20do%20is%20make%20sure%20people%20can%20still%20get%20access%20to%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou've%20had%20a%20couple%20of%20price%20hikes%20now.%20Why%20not%20do%20it%20all%20in%20one%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20We're%20not%20forecasting%20out%20into%20the%20future%20and%20preemptively%20increasing%20pricing.%20What%20we're%20doing%20is%2C%20roughly%20monthly%2C%20looking%20at%20the%20running%20average%20of%20purchase%20prices%20of%20memory%20and%20using%20that%20to%20set%20the%20price%20for%20the%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20your%20sales%20taken%20a%20hit%20as%20a%20result%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20I%20can't%20give%20exact%20numbers%2C%20but%20we%20do%20see%20noticeable%20decreases%20in%20specific%20products%20when%20we%20increase%20prices.%20It's%20just%20supply%20and%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20long%20as%20your%20computer%20is%20still%20working%2C%20you%20have%20some%20flexibility%20to%20wait%20a%20bit%20longer%20to%20decide.%20We%20expect%2C%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20people%20are%20going%20to%20slow%20down%20buying%20new%20computers%20to%20replace%20the%20current%20ones.%20As%20we%20average%20this%20out%20over%20the%20course%20of%20years%2C%20we're%20still%20going%20to%20see%20that%20demand%20is%20pretty%20steady.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAre%20you%20frustrated%20with%20suppliers%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20You%20have%20to%20look%20at%20capitalism%20as%20a%20machine%20and%20accept%20it%20for%20what%20it%20is%3B%20otherwise%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20constantly%20be%20frustrated%20trying%20to%20build%20a%20business.%20We%20understand%20why%20prices%20are%20increasing.%20It%20is%20the%20unfortunate%20reality%20of%20how%20this%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20do%20you%20hope%20it%20will%20die%20down%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Everyone's%20got%20different%20viewpoints%20on%20this.%20Towards%20the%20end%20of%202027%20into%202028%2C%20we%20know%20that%20there%20will%20be%20some%20substantial%20increases%20in%20memory%20manufacturing%20capacity%20from%20big%20suppliers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20know%20what%20demand%20will%20look%20like.%20It%20could%20be%20the%20case%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-data-centers-electricity-donald-trump-ratepayer-protection-pledge-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20data%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20bubble%20pops%2C%20and%20suddenly%20there's%20a%20massive%20excess%20of%20supply%2C%20which%20would%20be%20great%20for%20consumers.%20It%20could%20be%20the%20case%20that%20demand%20increases%2C%20and%20it%20could%20be%20even%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20say%20early%202028%20is%20our%20best%20guess%20at%20when%20things%20are%20going%20to%20start%20to%20go%20back%20to%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http